  "input": {
    "question_id": "Q2",
    "framework": "CAIQ",
    "text": "Are independent audit and assurance assessments conducted according to relevant standards at least annually?"
  },
  "outbound_response": "Yes. BNY's Audit Committee oversees a comprehensive system of internal controls and is directly responsible for the selection, appointment, compensation, retention and oversight of the independent registered public accountants engaged to perform audit, review or attestation services, and for annually evaluating KPMG, including its qualifications and independence [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-24-051895::Item_5#0151]. On an annual basis, the Audit Committee reviews and discusses with management the audited financial statements and management's assessment of internal control over financial reporting, and KPMG issues its report on the financial statements and the operating effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-24-051895::Item_5#0153]. KPMG is an independent public accounting firm registered with the PCAOB and conducts its audit in accordance with PCAOB auditing standards, including those governing Communications with Audit Committees and auditor independence [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-25-046216::Item_3#0152]. The Audit Committee's annual review of KPMG also considers KPMG's continued independence, its understanding of the financial services industry and BNY's business, and the professionalism, objectivity and integrity of the engagement team, supported by management's annual assessment of the firm [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-25-046216::Item_3#0150]. These responsibilities, including annual evaluation of the external auditor, are formally assigned to the Audit Committee [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-22-059759::Item_4#0140].",
